{
  "texts": [
    "Despite WEASEL 2.0 demonstrating more pairwise wins compared to RDST or QUANT in the MCM, its ranking appears higher (worse) than both in the CD when all 8 comparates are taken into account.",
    "In addition, H-IT has less pairwise wins than RDST in the MCM, yet shows the lower (better) rank in the CD.",
    "Relative performance on test suites is important when evaluating classifiers, but it does not necessarily generalise to new problems.",
    "There will be problem domains and specific applications where different classifiers will be the most effective.",
    "Furthermore, characteristics such as the variability in performance and the run time complexity of algorithms are also of great interest to the practitioner."
  ]
}